  "text": "• AMD64ARMOpenSSL Dataset. To align our experimental evaluation with state-of-the-art studies we built the AMD64ARMOpenSSL Dataset in the same way as the one used in [CITATION_1] . In particular, the AMD64ARMOpenSSL Dataset consists of a set of 95535 functions generated from all the binaries included in two versions of Openssl (v1 0 1f -v1 0 1u) that have been compiled for AMD64 and ARM using gcc-5.4 with 4 optimizations levels (i.e., -O[0-3]). The resulting object files have been disassembled using ANGR; we discarded all the functions that ANGR was not able to disassemble.",
